<h2 style='text-align:right; margin-bottom:-50px; color:#f63;'>James Britt</h2>

<img src='http://www.jamesbritt.com/assets/2009/4/15/self-portrait_los-angeles-06_med.jpg' alt='James Britt' style='float:right; padding:50px 0 30px 30px;' height='360px' />

I’m a software developer and writer living in "Scottsdale, Arizona":http://www.google.com/maps?q=Scottsdale,+AZ,+USA&sa=X&oi=map&ct=title. My primary development language is Ruby.

I run "Ruby-doc.org":http://www.ruby-doc.org, the main documentation site for the Ruby language. I also created "RubyStuff.com":http://www.rubystuff.com, where you can find a nice range of Ruby-themed paraphernalia.  You can never have too many Ruby T-shirts.


I was Editor-in-Chief for "Ruby Code &amp; Style":http://www.artima.com/rubycs for about a year.

I’ve written a number of technical articles for publications such as Dr. Dobbs and Linux Journal, and co-authored the book "Professional VB 6 &amp; XML":http://www.amazon.com/Professional-Visual-Basic-6-XML/dp/1861003323, and wrote most of the Web development section in Hal Fulton’s "The Ruby Way, 2nd ed":http://www.amazon.com/Ruby-Way-Second-Addison-Wesley-Professional/dp/0672328844/ref=pd_bbs_sr_1/102-3752774-8774509 .

I’ve some articles "here":http://www.jamesbritt.com/content , and you can read about some of my "software projects":http://www.jamesbritt.com/code as well


I've spoken at numerous Ruby conferences; some of these are available as video on the "Confreaks site":http://www.google.com/search?q=James+Britt+site%3Aconfreaks.com.

I’m President of "Neurogami":http://www.neurogami.com, a Ruby/JRuby application development company in Scottsdale, AZ.  Neurogami develops "JotBot":http://www.getjotbot.com, a sleek desktop time-tracking tool written in JRuby using the "Monkeybars":www.monkeybars.org library. 

My personal blog is "JamesBritt.com":http://www.jamesbritt.com

You can reach me at james@neurogami.com

I also hang out on the IRC channels #phx.rb, #rbp, #jruby, #ruby-pro, and #ruby-lang, on freenode

My favorite color is plaid, and I was born and raised "on an island in North America.":http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&geocode=&q=Ft.+Washington+Avenue,+10033&sll=40.855777,-73.944799&sspn=0.051416,0.084972&ie=UTF8&z=16&iwloc=addr



